{
  "texts": [
    "At least until ChatGPT launch, a few languages did not have a mainstream LLM support.",
    "This selective language support creates an ideal natural experiment setting, allowing us to compare innovation trajectories with and without LLM assistance.",
    "We compiled comprehensive datasets for both language pairs on which our analyses are performed from October 2019 to October 2022, a period spanning two years before and 1.25 years after the introduction of GitHub Copilot.",
    "For Python, Rust and Haskell packages, we focused our data collection on the 2000 most popular packages as of 2021.",
    "4 We obtained the entire list from R's central repository, the Comprehensive R Archive Network (CRAN), as we did not find a reliable index of well-maintained packages."
  ]
}